            <h2>How do you raise a complaint with KLM? </h2>
            <p> If something goes wrong, passengers can also file a KLM complaint directly through the online feedback form. The KLM airline website also has a feedback form. Whether it is a delay, baggage issue or concern about onboard experience, the airline has a dedicated team to handle all grievances professionally. This process is very transparent, and users often get a response within a few working days. You can also check and track the status of your case using the reference number given by the airline once your complaint is registered. </p>
            <h3>Special Assistance and Accessibility Support</h3>
            <p>The airline is committed to inclusive travel; if you or your loved one requires special assistance, KLM provides dedicated services such as wheelchair support, assistance for visually/deaf passengers, and mobility aid arrangements. It's best to inform KLM at least 48 hours before your flight to ensure everything is arranged properly. </p>
